content: Good app

I passed my exam this morning with an 85%, BUT(!!!) while this app is useful it is either out of date with the current question set or prioritizes the wrong parts of the actual 107, or both. For reference I was acing the mock tests this app presents averaging 95-98%. The 107 has lots and lots of airspace and sectional map questions including a bunch that dont show up here. I would not advocate using this as your sole or primary method of prep, but as an augment or 'on the go' its fine.

This app help me do a crash study for the exam which I passed this morning. It was extremely helpful, one of the best tools I used in my studying. However, I did run into a handful of questions on the test that were not included in this app. I think the question pool needs to be updated in the app. Those are the questions that I probably missed on my test. I only got an 87 score. I'd been practicing in doing hundreds of tests, always scoring above 93 on this app.

Just went through the FAA part 107 test. Only about 10 out of 60 questions were from this app's bank (or maybe I was just lucky lol). Make sure to study FAR/AIM, sectional charts, chart supplements, and PHAK. Other than that, it seemed like the app doesn't shuffle answers in study mode. Overall, I'm satisfied with this app.
Thank you this app worths every penny, however it needs to be improved with the current questions. Anyways IMHO this is a must have app for anybody planning to take drone pilot exam.

I passed the Part 107 Airman Knowledge test today with a 90% score. This app was my main resource for studying and practicing for the test. The layout is simple and easy to use, there's an option to see explanation for each of the answers which is great! I've seen so many resources online that charge up to $300 for a study course which I find absolutely ridiculous. I watched a few YouTube videos, read through the FAA study guide once, and worked this app for a few hours and that's all it took.

Passed my test on 8/10/2020 Give this app 5 stars for helping prepare you. If you memerize the questions and don't know how to read sectionals or weather charts you'll probably get a 50% from this alone.
Great app in preparing for your FAA 107 or recurrent test. I first used it to study for my FAA 107 now using it to restudy for my recurrent test.
Passed my UAG exam for Part 107 with a 93% thanks to this app!
This application was key to getting my certification. I highly recommend it.

The app and Prepware Online are Great preparation tools for your Part 107 test, I scored a 90% on my test. Please make sure you have solid understaing of sectional charts and airspace classification, the test is heavy with those questions. Spend some extra time and watch some youtube videos on them.

I am so grateful that I had this app recommended to me! I watched the videos, read the materials, etc. I *thought* I had a solid understanding of the information and could pass my Part 107 test. Then I downloaded this app. And although I did alright, I quickly realized I still had some gaps in my learning and strategy. I spent a few days hammering on my now readily-apparent weak points. And I passed my Part 107 with a 95%!!! It has my highest recommendation!

I passed my Part 107 test today with a %97. This app and the companion ASA study book were an important component of my studying, along with two prominent drone study guide videos on YouTube. This was a great investment and there were some questions that were word for word. I felt like this covered most of what I needed. However the only reason I didn't give this 5 stars is that there were several questions in areas this app did not cover at all. Still well worth the small investment.
Great resource for test prep
Helped me pass the FAA Exam!, Don't use this as your sole source of information but it is a great tool for memorization! Well worth the $5 price tag.

Fantastic prep app!! Passed my first test with 83% and then my recurrent test (2 years later) with 93%!! The developer keeps the app current with frequent updates so you can be sure the info is up to date. Couldn't be more happy with this app. The value you get for the money is insane!!
I used this app to study for both the certification and for the recertification test and passed both of them on the first try. I found this app to be comprehensively helpful for test preparation.
Great for studying
Helped me pass the 107 exam with a 95%! Outside of adding examples of questions using the supplemental charts basically has everything you need to pass the exam.

Used this app along with some other resources to study. Got a 97! A lot of the questions on the actual test were identical to the ones on here. The only thing I think would make it better is to have the legend along with the sectional chart questions.
Get this app if you are studying for your RPC. I used this as my primary means of studying and I got an 87% on my exam after using this app for a few days.
An exam of 60 questions. In the app you have enough. It makes it difficult to study because maybe there are questions that will not come on the exam

I just passed the faa 107 exam. A lot of questions in the app were also in the actual test. I passed with an 83 and I mostly used this app to do it. I would suggest buying a sectional chart also, it will explain airspace better than the study guide.
Passed. 92%
Fantastic App! I purchased the book and decided to get the app so I can stay in test mode. It works great, and gives options for test mode or study mode. I am sure to pass with it.
without a doubt helped me pass the test
I just scored a 92%. Many of the questions are exactly what's on the test. This app paired with drone up did the trick.
got a 92 on the exam and i only used this app to study uses the same sectional charts as those on the test and many questions are the same
great app. I used it to get my certification. just open it and study whenever you get a chance
Passed the official test
Everything you need to pass your Part 107 test. Great App!

I just took the test made 85% out of 100. Study material very beneficial and test is very tricky pay close attention on the wording. I would recommend this app for anyone wants to Acs on the test. I hope that helps.

Simple interface that gives you exactly what you need. Only app I've found that let's you select which Bank of questions, which is great because you can do a practice test right after finishing a chapter. However, these are the same exact questions as on the ASA Test Prep guide, and I was looking for a different set of questions to round out my knowledge. Supposedly includes most recent FAA updates but the app was last updated in Nov 2018 and most recent FAA update was Feb 2019.

App is well thought out with test and study modes. This is not meant to teach you, but as learning reinforcement. I recommend that you take the LinkedIn Learning or DroneU courses to learn the content and then use this app to practice for the test.
decent questions and maps same as other apps however no learning material or legends to speak of. this is strictly a practice test and not a method of education.

I like that it shows you if your answer is correct when you select it during study mode. I just took and passed my part 107. the test mainly has airspace questions (class b,c,d, ect.) and reading weather reports
Helped me prepare on the go and pass the 107. Very helpful! I recommend also purchasing the 2019 study guide on Amazon for $15. Together you will pass as well.
Not bad. Pretty bare bones but it helped me pass the 107. Beware, the wording on the actual test differs greatly from the questions on the app, but it will teach you what you need.
Everything good but , theres no option on taking the final test of the 60 questions....
I used this after not passing the first time. After the app I passed easily.
I have been trying to install the app for 2 days without any luck.

There are only two modes. Test and study.  Study has an "explanation" button to explain the question. Its not a traditional type of study where you read something first THEN take the test.   But the chart section seems to be functionally useless. It asks you what the class airspace is around a given airport, and refers you to the chart. The thing is, you need to the key to figure out what type of airspace the squiggly lines represent, and they don't show the key!    When you hit the explanation it says its "Class D" or "Class C" and cites the key.  But again, the key is not actually provided, so it really does no good. Maybe I am missing something but I don't see the key readily available.
This is not the correct way to learn. This app just has u memorize test questions it doesn't actually teach you anything.

I have had to start the practice test over four times. The software seems to ask me a lot of questions that I need to study more I have not yet been able to finish a test yet to grade it. This makes it ridiculous. It should auto save your current test.
Great app. Used it along with Tony Northrup's free YouTube study guide. PASSED.

I used this for the part 107 drone test. I spent about 4 hours on it using 
it on my smart phone and my tablet going through all the practice 
questions. The questions are sometimes identical to the ones that appeared 
on the actual exam. It more than prepared me for the exam through the 
repetition of questions, which is my preferred method of study. I could 
have studied much less and probably only done this app for a couple hours 
and still passed. I got a 95%. There are a lot of scams out there for the 
Drone test for $100 and $200 on the internet that probably aren't even as 
good and frankly borderline criminal.
Good job..

Doesn't have the correct answers to all of the questions which is probably 
what will make me remember those on the test, but what will I miss because 
I got a question right and it was really wrong.
Best app that I located for taking the 107 prep test.

Fantastically simple app with a lot of information. I used this app and a 
video by Tony Northrup for almost ALL of my studying. Took the test after 
only one week and got an 87%!
Seems pretty good. I'll find out first thing in the morning.

No frills study guide and cram material. I used it all the way up until the 
day I tested. When I started to pass the test mode consistently, I was 
really confident I was ready. Switching back and forth between charts and 
question text is a little wonky, and I wish it included an easy to use 
charts legend, but not enough to dock it a star.

Great app with mostly current testing questions. If you do well testing with this app you will pass the test. This is the only testing tool I paid for and passed with a 93%. My few small cons are their were two questions on the 107 test that are not addressed in this app. I wish there was a random category study option, for me too much similar info at once can start mixing together. A lot of the answer "explanations" are so technical or simply not elaborate enough to really help you learn. Finally the sectional chart legends are all available during 107 test but nowhere to be found in app.

Awesome! Simple method and just heads and shoulders above the rest. Especially appreciate the clear font in night mode which makes for good studying at bedtime.  The section on weather needs some improvements due to poor explanations for answers. Deduct 1 star for this.
This is all I studied and made 85 on exam.

I like this app! Just took my UAG test and got a 78% and I was getting 100s and 98s on the app. I would say 20% of prepware was not on the exam I got. By saying that, the explanations I got from this app helped me out indefinitely.
Best FAA part 107 app in the app store (of the 3 I tried). Explanation button helps to learn a concept and not just memorize questions.
Just passed the part 107 test and only used this app to prepare. Highly recommend!!!

Contains approximately 1/3 of the question pool and missing major subject areas. Also, a majority of the answer explanations are lame/limited and really doesn't explain anything - Meaning: This app teaches memorization and not critical thinking (as what the FAA wants).
Questions are fine. I'm red green color blind so study mode is difficult to determine if i got the right answer or not.

Excellent app just got fixed a little bit of the grammar. Q. (1051) remote Pilots are required to complete the following operational area surveillance prior to a sUAS flight. A. Keep the operational area free of and at an appropriate distance form all non-participants. ( Free off and at an) fix time
Wanted to thank Prepware. App was a great way to do my final round of studying. Passed the 107 so money well spent.Oh
Couldn't have passed the test without this.
Spent a couple weeks occasionally  prepping with the app. Just took the 60 question Part 107 exam and passed with an 87! I'm stoked. Great app! Thanks team for the help.

Great app passes the test with just this app. Questions are clpse enough to the real thing to get you through but get the suas test prep guide if you need basics the app does not teach those just reinforces what ypu study
Well worth the small price!
Very informative and helpful app. Perfect way to practice questions as a supplement to studying.
I find it easy to use and convenient, but I'm pretty sure at least one of the answers are incorrect.
Passed FAA Knowledge test
This is a great  app, I pass my part 107 test just by using this  app with a 80% on the test.. very happy  with  this.... thanks
Easy to have next to you on the phone to study up on the material. ..thanks !
New Galaxy S2 tablet. Needs work and to work if spending $$.
Wonderful tool, that is kept up to date and will enhance your knowledge!
At the last question in the test it stops - no Indication on how to get the score
Used this in addition to the FAA study guide and passed with 80 percent.  Great tool.
Need to fix the grading part but other then that it's great.
Facts are updated with latest guidance and the UI is very stable.  Initial impression is 5-Star for sure!  Nice work ~
During quiz mode and submit for grading it always shows you got 100% correct that needs to be fixed.
